snippet.title: 【mew & friends】"Fukashigi no Carte"  2020 ver.║ Bunny Girl Senpai ED ║ Full ENGLISH Cover & Lyrics
snippet.description:
This is our NEW 2020 cover of Fukashigi no Carte, the ED for Rascal Does not Dream of Bunny Girl Senpai! 

STREAM: https://lnkfi.re/FukashiginoCarte

I can finally say… after 2 years… let's bring this song to Spotify!!! Thank you guys all so much for the love on our original 2018 version, but because that version used the official instrumental, I was not able to do so. But because of the amazing instrumental work of Brandon Yates, we're able to go for it now! 

This is a totally remastered version of the previous cover with updated lines and (hopefully) upgraded audio quality - I really hope you guys enjoy! 

Please give a big thank you and send lots of love again to all of the amazing vocalists who were kind enough to join me in this project ♡ 

Eeveeon: http://bit.ly/2PpVigS
IN0RI: http://bit.ly/2ON4Frk
AirahTea: http://bit.ly/2qdrjKO
Mari: http://bit.ly/2OSjgBV
Luciana.a: http://bit.ly/2EMFXTo

Repeat extra special love to Eeveeon for the harms, Eeveeon for the translation and zzz - Anime on Piano for extra help with the translation ^^)/

If you enjoyed this cover, please consider liking and subscribing! It would make my day! ♡

► LYRICS:
I cannot speak, I cannot sleep, stuck in a daydream 
The one I see, is it reality?
It's written down in words I cannot read
I want to know, I only want to see
 
Lies and truth, tightly intertwined
Could it be? All of this is really true?
and they're just blind?
 
Am I just talking to myself?
Take it slow, please don't overwork yourself
All I want is to have your love
 
I'll say goodbye, I think it's time, as all the lights spin
Will I survive if you're not here with me?
It's written down in words no one can read
I want to know, but should I really see? 
 
Beating hearts, living in this world
And it hurts when you can't be next to me
Won't you return?
 
Every night, I will make a wish 
It's so clear, I just want to be with you
I beg you, please make this come true
 
It's so absurd, but it's so real, I can't believe it
filled with regret, cause you're not here with me
It's written down in words no one can read
Stuck on repeat, seemingly endlessly 
 
And a voice calls out to me
Am I waking from this dream?
Is it beautiful?
Should I be careful?
Is this what I want? 
Well, hey
Tell me!
 
I cannot speak, I cannot sleep, stuck in a daydream 
The one I see, is it reality?
It's written down in words I cannot read
I want to know, I only want to see
 
And now I'm stuck, there's no way out, here in this daydream
Stranded and lost, between realities
It's written down in words I cannot read
Time passing by, heart beating fast, as I want to know
I need to know, but should I really see?
